Withing this distance the tidal force will tear a moon apart.

$D=R_p\left(\frac{2\rho_p}{\rho_m}\right)^{\frac{1}{3}}$

where $\rho$ is density. It's the distance at which [planetary rings]() form from remains of broken up moons.

